00:10:51.350 --> 00:10:52.980
every odd positioned digit.

00:10:52.980 --> 00:10:55.560
So you add the first thing
they call out to the third

00:10:55.560 --> 00:10:56.810
to the fifth all the way up.

00:10:56.810 --> 00:10:58.360
And if you add
every second digit,

00:10:58.360 --> 00:11:00.910
starting in the first
position, you get a subtotal.

00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:03.400
You multiply that
subtotal by three,

00:11:03.400 --> 00:11:06.200
and then you go back and add on
the other digits you skipped.

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:08.408
And if you add every second
digit, multiply by three,

00:11:08.408 --> 00:11:10.810
add the other digits,
for all US barcodes,

00:11:10.810 --> 00:11:13.639
the grand total will
be a multiple of 10.

00:11:13.639 --> 00:11:15.180
And so if you keep
track in your head

00:11:15.180 --> 00:11:16.470
and there's one of the
missing at the end,

00:11:16.470 --> 00:11:18.840
it's whatever you need to
get-- OK now some of you

00:11:18.840 --> 00:11:20.695
