pick it up, jumble it around,

00:20:28.458 --> 00:20:30.860
put it down a different way,
make two crossings switches,

00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:32.399
see if it untangles itself.

00:20:32.399 --> 00:20:34.190
And actually, it's
really important that we

00:20:34.190 --> 00:20:36.270
know how to do this,
because at the moment

00:20:36.270 --> 00:20:39.010
bacteria is better
at undoing knots

00:20:39.010 --> 00:20:41.790
than humans, which is
a little bit worrying.

00:20:41.790 --> 00:20:44.030
Because when bacteria
reproduces-- in fact,

00:20:44.030 --> 00:20:45.980
same thing happens
with most cells,

00:20:45.980 --> 00:20:50.430
and human included-- the DNA
gets tangled and knotted.

00:20:50.430 --> 00:20:52.730
And so some bacteria
have circular DNA,

00:20:52.730 --> 00:20:54.430
gets very knotted
when they reproduce.

00:20:54.430 --> 00:20:56.960
And there are enzymes
which go around and perform

00:20:56.960 --> 00:20:58.630
crossing switches
exactly like that.

00:20:58.630 --> 00:21:01.430
They will snip one bit of DNA,
move it around another one,

00:21:01.430 --> 00:21:02.580
and rejoin it.

00:21:02.580 --> 00:21:04.600
And they do that
very efficiently

00:21:04.600 --> 00:21:05.530
to untangle the DNA.

00:21:05.530 --> 00:21:09.090
And if they can't do that,
the bacteria can't reproduce.

00:21:09.090 --> 00:21:11.490
And so knot theorists
from the maths department

00:21:11.490 --> 00:21:14.410
are working with biologists
to try and work out

00:21:14.410 --> 00:21:16.861
what the bacteria is doing,
why it's better than us,

00:21:16.861 --> 00:21:19.110
and if we get a better
understanding of both what it's

00:21:19.110 --> 00:21:21.620
doing and how to undo
knots in general, that

00:21:21.620 --> 00:21:23.530
could be a new wave
of antibiotics.

00:21:23.530 --> 00:21:26.310
If we have a way to
impede or stop bacteria

00:21:26.310 --> 00:21:28.170
from unknotting
its DNA, then we'll

00:21:28.170 --> 00:21:29.670
be able to stop it
from reproducing.

00:21:29.670 --> 00:21:31.044
And so I think
it's very exciting

00:21:31.044 --> 00:21:35.150
