00:45:18.800 --> 00:45:20.270
And that's very good question.

00:45:20.270 --> 00:45:22.700
The answer is no idea.

00:45:22.700 --> 00:45:26.330
So I'm not sure actually,
because what actually happens

00:45:26.330 --> 00:45:29.850
if you want to see the
way you get knots in DNA--

00:45:29.850 --> 00:45:30.670
you can try this.

00:45:30.670 --> 00:45:32.950
Because if anyone's
ever made a Mobius loop

00:45:32.950 --> 00:45:34.751
and then cut it
in half, you will

00:45:34.751 --> 00:45:36.500
find that you end up
with one longer loop.

00:45:36.500 --> 00:45:37.460
It's fascinating.

00:45:37.460 --> 00:45:40.050
If you have more twists,
you get longer loops

00:45:40.050 --> 00:45:41.260
that are tangled together.

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:42.560
And that's what's
happening with DNA.

00:45:42.560 --> 00:45:44.190
It's and incredibly
twisted molecule.

00:45:44.190 --> 00:45:45.430
Because it unzips
down the middle,

00:45:45.430 --> 00:45:47.138
but all those twists
means the two halves

00:45:47.138 --> 00:45:48.680
are all tangled
around each other.

00:45:48.680 --> 00:45:52.106
And so what the enzymes--
they're called tropo something

00:45:52.106 --> 00:45:56.550
undabellabella monase
and so what they're doing

00:45:56.550 --> 00:45:58.620
is-- I'm not a
biologist-- is working

00:45:58.620 --> 00:46:00.160
on a huge mass of this stuff.

00:46:00.160 --> 00:46:02.920
So I suspect they
never encounter knots

00:46:02.920 --> 00:46:06.492
that simple is my gut reaction.

00:46:06.492 --> 00:46:08.950
I think it's a bit like solving
like the traveling salesman

00:46:08.950 --> 00:46:09.450
problem.

00:46:09.450 --> 00:46:11.500
You've got good
strategies, but you

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:13.440
can't guarantee you've
done the best way,

00:46:13.440 --> 00:46:15.712
but it's incredibly
efficient in general.

00:46:15.712 --> 00:46:16.420
But I don't know.

00:46:16.420 --> 00:46:19.250
I will contact some biologists
and say, look, put down all

00:46:19.250 --> 00:46:21.080
this curing cancer stuff.

00:46:21.080 --> 00:46:23.220
We've got a knot
we've got to solve.

00:46:23.220 --> 00:46:24.960
And I'll report back.

00:46:24.960 --> 00:46:26.600
So on that note, I
am going to wrap up,

00:46:26.600 --> 00:46:28.800
but I will be loitering
around for as long as I can.

00:46:28.800 --> 00:46:30.508
I think I am going to
have to finish now.

00:46:30.508 --> 00:46:33.030
And so on that note, again,
